The paper deals with the Kolmogorov complexity of infinite binary sequences, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the concept of truth-table reduction, which is a common technique in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The study of infinite sequences is also related to the field of discrete mathematics (cs.DS). The paper also discusses randomness and the lack of effective procedures, which are topics in cryptography (cs.CR) and logic (cs.LO), respectively.
